comment:
she has indeed been paid for the film, but there is an "image" clause in most SAG contracts where if you bring too much bad publicity, and/or get charged with a crime the studio can cancel a contract for that. They would still have to pay a portion, but SHE would have broken their terms and they would have been free to replace her in the film with another actress. They have that right.. as they did it with/to JD... 

It exists to protect the studio in just such an occurrence. Wonder if they checked their fine print.. they probably DID include it in the contract it's more than likely buried in there (as it's been included in almost every legal SAG contract's fine print since the 40's). It IS pretty much a standard clause... for most SAG card holders contracts. Have they forgotten about it.. or are they just pretending they didn't remember?

comment:
Everything Amber Heard did, in case anyone is curious:

Once she found out Depp was filing for divorce, she defecated on his bed and claimed it was a prank.

She stole the story about how her former assistant was r*ped at knife point and used it falsely against Depp. Later, the story was found to be stolen and fabricated.

She had friends apply makeup to make herself appear bruised. The bruises were found to be fake and she lost much credibility.

She severed the tip of Depp's finger and crushed the bone with a vodka bottle after a fight. His finger required plastic surgery to fix and he almost lost it.

There is audio recordings of Heard admitting to abusing Depp, such as her punching him in the face, slamming his arm in a door, and the vodka bottle incident. There is also audio recording of her emotionally and verbally abusing Depp, calling him demeaning names such as "victim" and "cry-baby".

Heard has a previous domestic violence charge from her ex-girlfriend in 2009 who accused her of being abusive.

She sued Depp and promised to donate the money from the court case to a charity for abused women, but instead spent the money on unknown purchases, leading the court to favor Depp.

If all of these actions don't prove that Heard was the abusive one, I don't know what else she could do to make it any more obvious.
